{
  "stem": "3380.1",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I remember, that was on a Friday.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And people used to come, maybe about 40 kilometers away from our town, that the city was bombarded even before war was declared.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So people actually came without anything on them, to run away from the bombs.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we have seen, I mean, that there's a tragic thing approaching.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "What the end gonna be, we only know that the war started.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "How that's gonna end, where it's gonna end, and when it's gonna end, nobody knows.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] How were-- how-- how was Hitler's-- how was the invasion at this time?",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "You talk about how the Jews felt about it.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "How did the non-Jews feel about this?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "When the Germans came into our town, the Polish population, some of them, pointed out where Jews are living.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Or if we stayed in line, some of the Polacks also pointed out the Jews are in line.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They-- they had to move.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They had to go back-- either to the back of the line, or they chased them away from the line.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I mean, they were not too friendly.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Not to us.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We didn't have any contact before the war with too many Poles.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And we haven't got any contact there.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 7 SECONDS]",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 64,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "At any time?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 66,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "When the war broke out, on November the 11th-- that usually was a-- a holiday.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 66,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because on November 11, the Poles were liberated after 125 years being under the Russian and the German occupation.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 66,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So that-- that was a day, like, we've got the 4th of July.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 66,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The Germans came, and they took the-- the rabbi and the Jewish people into the marktplatz.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 66,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "That was a place.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 66,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And they used to make a comedy show.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 66,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "You know, they used to beat the Jews.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
